@AlexCDev @leonardjfrench There is a takedown-request form on the website if you want copyrighted metadata removed.
@crablabuk Spoke too fast. With nfts, the metadata is not stored onchain. The metadata is what is visible on platforms like Opensea.
@crablabuk There is a takedown-request on the website to remove copyrighted work from the metadata.
@aaronreynolds I have been informed this has been worked on. Kindly confirm on your end.
@aaronreynolds @EffinBirds @edent I will get in contact with them and get it sorted in an hour or 2
@aaronreynolds @EffinBirds @edent Your work has been deleted. The guys at opensea can get the rest i.e your username and links unavailable on their platform.

@aaronreynolds @EffinBirds @edent That site isn't ours. It just pulls every non fungible token in existence on the blockchain and displays it and lets people transfer/exchange. Once its minted on the blockchain we cannot delete the text parts. We can remove the image part though and that is what we did.

@aaronreynolds @EffinBirds @edent Your interpretation of that is quite off. I can assure you that is not the case. No rights involved here at all. That is merely a link to a post that was archived on the blockchain. Without an image its just some random words with no context.
@aaronreynolds @EffinBirds @edent Show me the images. Those were not previews, they were the actual images. What is left for sale are blank white jpegs. I keep saying the same thing.
@EffinBirds @edent All images/cartoons removed. All 19 of them. Check below https://t.co/B2QYuCT0qe

@edent I will remove your tweets' screenshots so they don't appear on Opensea.
@edent If one of your followers decides to turn your public statements into a tokenized memory, they are doing it for other reasons and not to make money.

@edent The service is geared towards preserving history and truth mainly from public figures, politicians and celebrities. It is impractical to try getting access to them so they can "opt" in to have their public statements on a public social media site memorialized.

@edent Images can be prevented from appearing on Opensea, but the words cannot be deleted from the blockchain. Copyright regarding tweets is an ongoing debate 
https://t.co/YxrQidRUb7
@edent Yes, and we are working on a way where the original tweet author gets a cut from all future sales, not just the original sale.

@edent The reality is that most tweets have no historical significance/perceived value and will never be exchanged/traded and can just be treated as a stamp of approval. "I thought your joke was amazing so I turned it into a digital memory"
@edent Theoretically any token can be traded, if you can find a buyer who sees value in owning the particular digital memory.

@edent The service is used to archive historical moments and create a "digital memory" mainly from celebrities/public figures, ie Trump's tweets. It is not a claim on anyone's work. There is no automatic profit from archiving a twitter post.
@edent @tweetNFTs Blocking @tokenizedtweets worked. They won't be archived going forward.
